re of gender, now it is a form of gender. Engaging and rigorously argued, Trans Kids underscores the centrality of ever more particular configurations of gender in both our physical and psychological lives, and the increasing embeddedness of personal identities in social institutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aTransgender childrenzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aaffirming gender nonconformity.  aaffirming trans identity.  aatypical gender expression.  aatypical gender.  afacilitating gender.  afailure of gender.  afamilial acceptance of trans identity.  afeminism gender sexuality.  agender acquisition.  agender and sex.  agender and sexuality.  agender expression.  agender identity.  agender ideology.  agender nonconforming kids.  agender studies.  agender.  algbt.  algbtq.  aqueer families.  aqueer nonfiction.  aqueer studies.  aqueer theory.  atrans kids.  atrans.  atransgender kids.  atransgender.  atransitioning gender.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106676770 cprintz978052027503440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520964167?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520964167423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520964167/original  a978-3-11-066767-7  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY